AB  - The Lake Victoria Environmental Management Project of Burundi and Rwanda had a moderately unsatisfactory overall outcome, a moderately unsatisfactory performance by the Bank and the monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. The lessons learned were: (1) The ambition regarding what can be achieved at the project level needs to be realistic. (2) Selectivity and sequencing are important to achieve demonstrable results. (3) Ownership of investments is critical to their sustainability. (4) Proactive measures reduce fiduciary risks in times of political crisis. (5) Weak country systems and coordination can lead to unanticipated consequences.
