AB  - The overall outcome of the Agricultural Productivity Program for Southern Africa (APPSA) Project is moderately satisfactory, with moderately satisfactory Bank performance and modest monitoring and evaluation quality. The following are key lessons based on the APPSA implementation and achievements: 1. Strong partnerships with the Consultative Group for International Agricultural Research (CGIAR) centers, the private sector and producer organizations are essential to successfully increase technology generation and uptake. 2. The potential impact of agricultural technology generation and dissemination Research and Development (R and D) activities is enhanced when dissemination and delivery mechanisms are developed and considered earlier on. 3. Regional R and D project can catalyze a strong culture of regional collaboration, facilitating applied research to efficiently address shared problems with shared solutions.
