AB  - Ratings of PROIRRI Sustainable Irrigation Development Project for Mozambique were as follows: outcome was moderately satisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: (i) Self-sustainability of Water User Associations (WUAs); (ii) Crop mix and rate of utilization of irrigated land is important for the overall economic viability of irrigation investment; (iii) Provision of Technical Assistance(TA) for budding organizations and right skill sets are critical for project delivery; and (iv) Market-driven irrigation investment could drive smallholder commercialization.
