AB  - Ratings of Water for Agro-pastoral Livelihoods Pilot (WALP) Project for Somaliland were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was highly satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. Some of the lessons learned include: (i) addressing water fragility in FCV context is complex and not without risks; (ii) investments in institutional capacity building at all levels is critical to sustainability of investments; (iii) evidence-based, objective criteria-driven is critical to effective site selection; (iv) the wadi evaluation tool (WET), developed under the WALP project provided a valuable contribution to the process of finding potential areas for wadi water harvesting installations; (v) resources needed for supervision support and logistical challenges in FCV contexts should not be underestimated; and (vi) developing and mobilizing cost-effective, fit-for-purpose M&E systems in FCV settings is challenging.
