AB  - Ratings of the Second Phase of the Conservation Areas for Biodiversity and Development Project for Mozambique were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: Continuous Institutional Capacity Building and Strengthening institutions like National Administration of Protected Areas (ANAC) and BIOFUND are crucial for sustainable conservation efforts; Conservation depends on formal and effective community engagement and long-term engagement in the landscape approach; Land use planning is another core factor in conservation efforts; Collaborative Management Partnership (CMP) model in Mozambique helped integrate local communities, private entities, and Non- Governmental Organizations (NGOs) into enhanced biodiversity conservation; and Simplifying procurement processes and decentralizing clearances was crucial in Matching Grant Scheme (MGS).
