AB  - The Water Management and Development Project for Uganda had a satisfactory outcome. Bank performance was moderately satisfactory while M&E Quality was modest. The project development objectives were to improve (i) integrated water resources planning, management and development; and (ii) access to water and sanitation services in priority urban areas. The project will contribute to higher level goals of sustaining natural resources, improving service delivery, and increasing economic productivity. The PDO indicators were not formally revised during project implementation. The components were not formally revised. However, the scope of components one and two was reduced for two reasons. Some lessons learned during the project include: Assist the client to build capacity as early as possible; Restructure as soon as a required change in design or scope is known; and Maintain a focus on delivering services to the end customer.
