AB  - Ratings for the Second Phase of the Fourth Transformation of Agriculture Sector Program-for-Results (PforR) for Rwanda were as follows: outcome and Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was modest. Some lessons learned included: PforR instrument can be a great tool to support policy reforms and transformational interventions. PforRs should integrate a gradual process for delivery of introduced reforms and other best practices. Public-private partnerships in productive alliances can sustain smallholder farmers linkages to markets. Increased capacity for developing commercially viable projects and a legal framework integrating agribusiness contextual aspects will be critical for sustainable and profitable investments.
