AB  - Ratings of Shire River Basin Management Program Project for Malawi were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: (i) Reversing watershed degradation requires significant investment in strengthening institutional capacities at all levels; (ii) A community-led landscape approach to watershed restoration can achieve results at scale and help build resilience at basin scale; (iii) Improving water resources management requires a combination of investments in institutions, information and infrastructure; (iv) Choices about project design and scope should consider the capacity of implementing agencies; and (v) Inter-agency collaboration on multi-sectoral projects requires strong government commitment and deliberate design choices.
