AB  - Ratings of National Agricultural and Rural Inclusive Growth Project for Kenya were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: the lead farmer model of technology transfer and extension encourages community building and strengthening, and peer to peer learning; Delivering TA via multiple channels is crucial; Market linkages and access to finance is key; Excellent implementation is crucial in a devolved context; and Building strong institutions is crucial for sustainability.
