AB  - Ratings for the Agricultural Support and Fiscal Management Development Policy Financing for Malawi were as follows: overall outcome and achievement of objectives (efficacy) was moderately satisfactory and relevance of prior actions was satisfactory. Some lessons learned included: there should be a reconsideration in Malawi on the way prior actions and results indicators are defined and agreed upon. Strengthening linkages with Bank technical assistance (TA) and investment lending operations, when possible, will support implementation and supervision of the development policy operation (DPO). A DPO series needs to adequately account for a lengthy process of legislative change. The analysis in the implementation completion and results (ICR) indicates that in Malawi it takes a long time to implement legislative change.
