AB  - Ratings of Agribusiness and Trade Project for Zambia were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. Some of the lessons learned include: Matching grants can be effective if sufficient resources are invested in the selection and coaching of beneficiaries; Mentoring and role of customized support is vital; Working with intermediaries can be very successful in reaching small farmers; working with distributors was important for SMEs; Importance of working capital; and Such projects should focus more on job creation and income growth as the key development outcome.
