AB  - Ratings for the Governance for Competitiveness Technical Assistance Project for Rwanda were as follows: outcomes were moderately satisfactory, risk to global environment outcome was moderate, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and Borrower performance was moderately satisfactory. Some lessons learned included:(1) The results chain should be credible; (2) The assessment of capacity and timeframes during design and implementation should be realistic; (3) Relatedly, appraisal of uncertainty should also be realistic; (4) Sequencing and complementarity should be carefully assessed and leveraged; and (5) Projects could actively foster sustainable government collaboration.
