AB  - Ratings for the Agricultural Growth Program Project for Ethiopia were as follows: outcomes were moderately unsatisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality performance was modest. Some lessons learned included: Private sector actors successfully implemented Small-Scale Irrigation (SSI) schemes, exceeding targets.Exchange visits can serve as an effective mechanism to convince policy-makers to consider new initiatives that have worked in other places with a similar context.The success of capacity-building activities in the project can be enhanced using a more consistent, uniform approach.The project demonstrated how agricultural growth originated at the ground level through the (Common Interest Group) CIGs.Creating and strengthening CIGs is an effective way to mainstream gender into projects.Group formation and collective action are necessary, but not sufficient conditions, to achieving agricultural commercialization in Ethiopia.
