AB  - Rating of Agriculture Rehabilitation and Recovery Support Project for Congo, Democratic Republic of were as follows: outcome was moderately satisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. Some of the lessons learned include: (i) Careful attention to Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) from the project start is essential; (ii) Need for prudence in the setting of Project Development Objective (PDO) and intermediate results targets in large post-conflict countries; (iii) Yield measurements should be complemented by measurement of cropping patterns and area of land cultivated; (iv) Major executing agencies need special supervision arrangements; (v) Use of local World Bank staff on the ground should be increased; (vi) The involvement of public entities in charge of certain public goods is essential as it can help build capacity while serving as a vehicle for sustainability; (vii) Breakthroughs in agricultural technology should be accompanied by supportive policy measures; and (viii) Need for timeliness in additional financing.
