AB  - Ratings of Land Administration Project for Mozambique (Terra Segura) were as follows: outcome was moderately satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include:hiring of firms to carry out an independent quality assurance of the work and support the implementation of environment and social safeguard aspects; the formulation and adoption of the 2023 National Land Policy and the drafting of the new Land Law provide valuable lessons for other governments; and experience from the World Bank’s projects involving significant investments in land reform, land titling, institutional changes, and development of information systems indicates that they take longer than the ‘typical five years’ allocated.
