AB  - Ratings for the Statistics Project for Comoros were as follows: overall outcomes were satisfactory, bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some lessons learned included: the project was linked to the government Strategy for Accelerating Growth and Sustainable Development (SCA2D) and the 2015-19 NSDS which raised the importance of strengthening statistical national capacity and underscored the need for continued capacity building support. The management of INSEED and the government were also consulted during project design to identify their needs. This has contributed to smooth implementation of the project activities. The project combined methodological improvements through technical assistance and training, equipment, and information communication technology (ICT) upgrading. It helped to initiate the use of technologically advanced methods for data collection with the transition from the use of PAPI to CAPI and the digitization of the enumeration areas during primary sample units’ maps. The following intermediate indicator was not met, organizing focus groups to provide feedback on the quality, relevance, and timeliness of statistics- A more concrete indicator measuring improvement in the production and dissemination of statistics would be easier to implement and measure.
