AB  - Rating of Agricultural Productivity and Diversification Project for Benin were as follows: outcomes were satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and Borrower performance was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: (i) A strong private sector involvement in the seed production system is key to improving the supply of planting materials to producer; (ii) Creating an enabling environment is key for increased private sector investments in the value chains; (iii) Key institutional reforms in the agricultural sector are important for empowering producers’ apex organizations and interprofessional bodies; and (iv) Access to finance, availability of inputs, and efficient advisory services are key ingredients for fostering the adoption of productivity-enhancing technologies and food and nutrition security.
