AB  - Ratings of Health Services Reinforcement Project for Burkina Faso were as follows: outcome was moderately unsatisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: Tailoring Project Scope to Local Contexts especially in Fragility, Conflict and Violence Context; Early and continuous involvement of local authorities, communities, and other stakeholders played a pivotal role in the successful implementation of health and nutrition interventions; Improving quality and coverage of health services through strategic purchasing; and Strengthening investments in disease surveillance.
