AB  - Ratings of Third Phase of Regional Disease Surveillance Systems Enhancement Project for Benin, Mali, Mauritania, and Niger were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: A regional approach is vitally important for health security; Operationalizing One Health requires a dedicated technical organization and a shift in institutional roles across countries; Using globally accepted indicators can help align projects with higher-level objectives, but it also poses challenges; Regional projects involving FCV countries need flexible designs and extra implementation support; Sustainability planning should begin early in the project and be finalized by the MTR; and Strengthening the supply of and demand for health security professionals across IHR core capacity requirements is essential to sustain the development of the regional, national, and sub-national ecosystem and to include more women and youth in this important field.
