L1  - C:\Users\mlolita\OneDrive - CGIAR\WP2_Evidence Synthesis\Grey Literature\Data\Project_doc\Worldbank\Docs\2015_2026\worldbank_P159476_34048813_ICR_2023.pdf
AB  - Ratings for the Livestock Sector Development Support Project for Burkina Faso were as follows: outcomes were satisfactory, the Bank performance was satisfactory, and the monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some lessons learned included: when defining indicators for livestock herd improvement programs, it is important to critically account for all the elements along the entire chain to adequately calibrate the time needed for successful implementation. Herd improvement programs, especially when starting from a very low infrastructural and human capacity base, require a lot of pre-requisites, including establishing the appropriate physical and logistical infrastructure (adequately equipping multiplication centers and decentralized handling facilities, acquiring high performance breeding stock and appropriate climate-controlled transportation mechanisms, etc.), and training staff at all levels. The gestation period of animals needs to be fully accounted for as well. All this helps in setting realistic expectations of the levels of productivity achievable during the project’s implementation period. It is important to address issues as they arise instead of waiting for mid-term review. The case of the indicators that needed adjustments to sharpen attribution or set realistic expectations is instructive. Waiting for mid-term review to act can create missed opportunities for timely intervention. Constantly recalibrating aspects of the project as and when the need for corrective measures is detected is highly recommended. Like Productive Alliances, innovation platforms should be initiated as early as possible in the project cycle. They require extensive consultation and ownership for their successful establishment. In this case, because of the lengthy consultation process, they were established towards the project’s closing, thus limiting their contribution to project outcomes within the project’s implementation period.
KW  - Burkina Faso
