AB  - Ratings for the Livestock Development Project for Cameroon were as follows: outcome and Bank performance was satisfactory and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was modest. Some lessons learned included: flexibility when implementing complex and novel programs is essential. Flexibility when implementing complex and novel programs is essential. The trade-off between implementing more complex and novel designs with implementation capacity needs to be carefully considered.
