AB  - The development objective of the Agriculture Sector Support Project for Guinea is to strengthen the capacity of selected sector institutions to support the effective implementation of the recipient's national agriculture and food security investment plan (PNIASA). The project comprises of two components. The first component is strengthening of sector management capacities. The second component is analytical support to PNIASA implementation. The project facilitated the preparation of sub-programs based on analytical studies and three master plans that allowed two sectoral ministries (agriculture and livestock) to have key investment plans to inform the design of new operations or negotiate future operations.
