AB  - Ratings for the Agro-Processing Competitiveness Project for Sierra Leone were as follows: outcomes were satisfactory, the Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and the monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. Some lessons learned included: for projects implemented in countries with fragility and significant fiscal constraint, it is crucial to embed the sustainability of project activities in the design of the project to sustain impact. The project could have been more proactive in planning for sustainability, as some key MDAs had limited capacity in core areas. For example, SMEDA staff could have been embedded at the TA Facility to ensure transfer of knowledge on the SME development program. Similarly, the MTI technical staff could have had stronger collaboration with the PCU to build practical project management and coordination expertise. This would have been particularly beneficial given the high turnover of ministers affected by cabinet reshuffles and a change in the Government due to a general election. Going forward, the Government of Sierra Leone will need to ensure a closer link between fiduciary and technical aspects of a given project. While the centralized PFMU model could in principle lead to efficiency gains and closer oversight of projects by the MOF, it will need to be better integrated with the PCUs, have a clear operation manual to guide its operations, and have a clear and transparent funding mechanism to sustain its operation to minimize delays and avoid reporting gaps. This is especially true for the procurement function, which requires that technical staff are aware of the procurement stage for any given activity and are part of evaluation committees. The project, in line with previous research findings, has shown that good-quality TA to SMEs can be beneficial and help optimize the impact of business grants. Finally, clear and regular communication around project achievements and status is essential to ensure satisfaction of both direct and indirect beneficiaries.
KW  - Sierra Leone
