AB  - Ratings for the Africa Higher Education Centers of Excellence Project for Western Africa were as follows: outcome and Bank performance was satisfactory and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was substantial. Some lessons learned included: results-based financing can be a powerful mechanism for incentivizing effort and behavior change when used appropriately. Strong institutional ownership is an essential component for a successful center of excellence model. Leadership plays an important role in the center of excellence model. National efforts to reform higher education systems will be essential to complement efforts made by the Project for sustained results. Increasing participation of women will require greater attention. Strengthened linkages with the private sector will be important for knowledge transfer. There is a need to expand the role of the Regional Facilitation Unit (RFU) beyond its core mandate tasks of verification, implementation support, and technical assistance. Extensive multi-layered implementation support is important for success of a large regional project.
