AB  - Ratings for the First, Second and Third Grant Shared Growth Project for Niger were as follows: outcomes were moderately unsatisfactory, the risk to development outcome was significant, the Bank performance was moderately unsatisfactory, and the Borrower performance was also moderately unsatisfactory. Some lessons learned included : It is beneficial to tie a Development Policy Operation (DPO) into relevant investment operations to help both operations achieve better outcomes.Electricity reform requires the proper institutional setup prior to tariff changes to ensure appropriate rate adjustments and successful implementation. When institutional capacity at sector ministries is limited, it is advisable toconcentrate on a limited number of ministries to improve the prospects for Program outcomes.Procurement verification needs to be more than a one-time effort to beeffective. It is also necessary to have sustained follow-up and monitoring if auditfunctions are to be improved.To be able to better evaluate program results, it is important to haveindicators that are closely related to the prior actions.
