L1  - C:\Users\mlolita\OneDrive - CGIAR\WP2_Evidence Synthesis\Grey Literature\Data\Project_doc\Worldbank\Docs\2015_2026\worldbank_TG-Togo_Emergency_Covid-19_DPO_2021_--_P174376_Implementation_Completion_and_Results_Report_2022.pdf
AB  - Ratings for the Emergency Covid-19 Development Policy Financing for Togo were as follows: overall outcome, achievement of objectives (efficacy), and Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and relevance of prior actions was satisfactory. Some lessons learned included: when dealing with a crisis, operations should focus on new priorities of the Government to manage the shock. Operations should target crucial measures addressing direct and indirect impacts of the crisis. Use of digital is key for resilience in face of shocks and can play a determinant role in the success of a reform. However, where mobile internet penetration is low, digital transition should be gradual. In times of crisis, balancing ambition and realism is crucial. Complex reforms should be avoided, and implementation of prior actions should be supported by technical assistance and projects. Information-sharing and strong political will are critical in times of crisis. Transparent and well-coordinated partnerships can also be used as a major driving force. Supervision of prior actions implementation post disbursement is critical and should become systematic. Formulation of results indicators and targets should be relevant and measurable in a low data environment.
