AB  - Ratings of Infrastructure for Urban Development and Competitiveness of Second Cities Project for Côte d'Ivoire were as follows: outcome was moderately satisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. Some of the lessons learned include: the project’s focus on improving competitiveness in secondary cities like Bouaké and San Pedro was innovative, serving as a template for similar operations in the region and crowding-in donor interest in supporting secondary cities in Côte d’Ivoire; the importance of continued local and national buy-in, including citizen engagement; procurement, contract management, and the importance of implementation readiness; strengthening M&E frameworks; effective MSME support but challenges with matching grants; and sustainability and innovation in MSME financing.
