AB  - Ratings of Sustainable Livelihoods for Returnees and Host Communities in the Senegal River Valley Project for Mauritania were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was modest. Some of the lessons learned include: (i) the importance of conducting a rigorous market assessment prior to vocational training; (ii) the value of carrying out a full-fledged cost-benefit analysis during appraisal to ensure economically sustainable livelihoods; (iii) complementing support for economic activities with basic social services; and (iv) clustering small farmers or community groups to promote economy of scale.
