AB  - Ratings of Integrated Public Sector Reform Project for Congo, Republic of were as follows: outcome was satisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: The implementation schedule of governance programs should be sufficiently long and flexible; Proper establishment and capacitation of the Project Coordination Unit (PCU) with clear institutional setup and labor division before effectiveness is critical; World Bank project leads should ideally be based in country to make them easily accessible to PCU/Project Implementation Unit (PIUs); High-level political commitment and champions of reform are vital elements for the project's success but can often be a vulnerability; For a low-capacity environment, from the onset, the project design should be simple and easy to follow with a clearly defined scope and theory of change; and On the rollout of digital systems, the project design should be comprehensive from end to end and strictly target the achievement of the ultimate outcomes and not outputs.
