AB  - Ratings for the Second Land Administration Project for Ghana were as follows: outcome and Bank performance was moderately satisfactory and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was modest. Some lessons learned included: it is necessary to prepare and consider lessons from previous projects prior to finalizing the preparation of the next phase. Land projects are complex, expensive, and time consuming but highly beneficial if they are successfully completed. Major information technology (IT) systems are notorious for not being completed within a five-year project cycle. The process of customary land demarcation and surveying was expensive and complex. It is not clear that the benefits outweighed the costs, and the process brought to light a boundary conflict that was previously dormant.
