AB  - Some of the lessons learned in First Fiscal Management, Competitiveness, and Energy Reform Development Policy Financing Project of Guinea were as follows: (i) Sectoral diversification can help hedge against high political and governance risk, however there are tradeoffs with capacity constraints; (ii) The drawbacks of a low-capacity environment can be partly overcome by well-coordinated partnerships and complementary operations; (iii) Assuring sound results indicators while controlling for cofounding factors polluting results measurement is crucial; and (iv) In a low ‘monitoring and evaluation’ capacity context, selecting comprehensive, well-defined, and already regularly published indicators should be prioritized.
