AB  - Ratings for the Nigeria for Women Project (NFWP) were as follows: outcome was moderately satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was substantial. Some lessons learned included: the NFWP was a pilot designed to test Women Affinity Group (WAGs’) ability to promote women’s social and economic empowerment at the community and household levels, in line with the economic recovery and growth plan. Beyond their critical savings and loans activities, WAGs can also tackle broader challenges. The WAG system should eventually foster women’s full financial inclusion through commercial banks. WAGs are not one-time projects, but a first phase of larger programs or Series of Projects (SOPs). Providing grants to WAGs to establish revolving funds as a permanent feature of WAG financial operations, as opposed to individual microgrants to WAG members, is more efficient. WAGs offer a platform for supporting social services more extensively.
KW  - Nigeria
