AB  - Ratings for the Third Village Community Support Project for Guinea were as follows: outcome and Bank performance was satisfactory and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was substantial. Some lessons learned included: strengthened stakeholder ownership and accountability at all levels and capacity building at the grassroots are vital for the long-term sustainability of local government actions. Enhancing the institutionalization of participatory local development and service delivery is key to ensuring sustainable local governance. Bottom-up participatory models are effective tools for conducting strategic policy dialogue to advance long-term decentralization vision. Improved financial management systems - to facilitate fiscal transfers, manage tax revenues and fees, and possibly take advantage of commercial banking facilities - are key for effective decentralization.
