AB  - Ratings for the Growth and Competitiveness Project for The Gambia were as follows: outcomes were moderately satisfactory, risk to global environment outcome was significant, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and Borrower performance was moderately satisfactory. Some lessons learned included: (i) the focus was on business environment improvement and support to two economic clusters– horticulture and tourism; (ii) both the institutional design (Project Steering Committee and Tourism Marketing Committee) and targeted beneficiaries (out-growers, Micro, Small and Medium Enterprise (MSMEs), The Gambia Tourism and Hospitality Institute) demonstrate the emphasis on public-private partnerships; (iii) inter-ministerial coordination and ownership had some challenges in implementation due to frequent cabinet reshuffles that occurred during the project; (iv) establishing an independent Project Coordination Unit and building capacity of the Ministry of Economic Planning and Industrial Development (MEPID); and (v) Growth and Competitiveness Project (GCP) design built on existing initiatives regarding both sections of the Project Development Objective (PDO), the business environment improvement and economic cluster strengthening with the matching grant facility.
