AB  - The Rural Community-Drive Development Project of Guinea-Bissau had a satisfactory outcome. Bank performance was also satisfactory. The M&E Quality was substantial. The project development objective was to increase access to priority basic economic and social infrastructure and services. The Project was restructured twice and received two additional financing and responded to the country’s emerging and emergency needs. The Project received total financing of US 38.5 million dollars, and the closing date was extended from a planned 5 years to 10 years and closed on September 20, 2019. Some recommendations and lessons learned during the project include: Looking beyond the government to stimulate local development; High-level commitment is essential for managing sensitive political issues; Close monitoring and supervision; and Phased rollout informed challenges and appropriate adjustments to be made before scaling-up.
