AB  - The Competitiveness and Integrated Growth Opportunity Project on Benin had a satisfactory overall outcome, a satisfactory performance by the Bank and the monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. The lessons learned were: (1) Project design should be simple and aligned with the Government’s priorities. (2) Sustained Government commitment and ownership are key to successful project implementation. (3) Institutional and implementation arrangements should be clear and transparent. (4) Dedicated CMU’s support plays a critical role in successful implementation. (5) Strong leadership by TTL, profound technical skills, strategic vision, integrity and innovative approach to problem solving are key characteristics contributing to a successful project restructuring. (6) Monitoring indicators in the Results Framework should be realistic in attribution and achievable during implementation. (7) Proactive supervision and monitoring by both the Government and the World Bank contribute to a successful project implementation. (8) Under some conditions, the World Bank had capacity for a successful turnaround or poorly performing projects.
