AB  - Ratings of Desert Locust Response Project for Yemen were as follows: outcome was moderately satisfactory, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. Some of the lessons learned include: Even under the most difficult conditions, it is possible to establish basic operational capacity in a relatively short period; Attention to the sustainability of project outcomes is needed from the outset; Operational flexibility in technical solutions is key to addressing emerging implementation challenges; Regional coordination is an essential integral element of locust control programs; and Strategic partnerships are vital for the World Bank Group’s model of engagement in conflict-affected settings.
