AB  - The overall outcome of the Rural Community Development and Water Mobilization Project for Djibouti is highly satisfactory, with satisfactory Bank performance and substantial monitoring and evaluation quality. The Project provided the following lessons: (a) A robust Results Framework (Theory of Change) and sequencing of activities were critical for the project’s success; (b) The community-based, territorial approach was the right tool to achieve the expected results; (c) Beneficiaries’ contribution to Income-generating activities (IGAs) strengthened their ownership of these activities and the likelihood of success and (d) Accessible innovation and advisory services are key for sustainable agriculture and livestock development.
