AB  - The Modernization of Irrigated Agriculture in the Oum Er Rbia Basin of the Middle East and North Africa had a moderately satisfactory outcome, moderately satisfactory performance by the Bank and the monitoring and evaluation quality was substantial. The lessons learned were: (1) Careful selection of irrigation sectors to modernize. (2) Long duration of works typical of modernization in large scale irrigation calls for long implementation period. (3) Targeting small farmers calls for tailored procedures. (4) Drip irrigation requires an efficient water service. (5) Design of the network should be done having its operation in mind. (6) Performance-based indicators are key to the management of service delivery improvement.
