AB  - Ratings for the Integrated Irrigation Improvement and Management Project for Egypt were as follows: outcomes were moderately unsatisfactory, risk to global environment outcome was moderate, Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and Borrower performance was moderately satisfactory. Some lessons learned included: (i) Design projects more realistically by limiting outcomes to project’s direct influence; (ii) Be ready for implementation with priority contracts ready to be tendered; (iii) Irrigation management and infrastructure improvements must go hand in hand; (iv) Beneficiaries’ participation enhance benefits; (v) Procurement of civil works and contract management could be improved with larger procurement packages; (vi) Transparency and accountability are core elements of performance management and service delivery; and (vii) Sustainability beyond maintenance of works may require legal changes.
