L1  - C:\Users\mlolita\OneDrive - CGIAR\WP2_Evidence Synthesis\Grey Literature\Data\Project_doc\Worldbank\Docs\2015_2026\worldbank_MA-Strengthening_Agri-Food_Value_Chains_--_P158346_Implementation_Completion_and_Results_Report_2025.pdf
AB  - Ratings for the Strengthening Agri-Food Value Chains Project for Morocco were as follows: overall efficacy is rated modest, the Bank performance was moderately satisfactory, and the monitoring and evaluation quality is rated modest. Some lessons learned included the following: for activities requiring coordination and agreement among multiple stakeholders, the underlying institutional and implementation arrangements should be based on prior technical studies at the program's outset. Several of the Program’s technically innovative activities involving the construction of infrastructure and the operationalization of new services/management models (establishment of the CIA, construction of the wholesale market, and the Ceratitis center) were delayed as the related governance agreements between the designated implementing entities were put in place without the prior agreement of the involved parties on specific operational aspects and sufficient grounding in technical studies. Efforts to develop financing and operational arrangements were not started until advanced construction stages. Technical studies clarifying operational and financial elements should be completed before the construction phase initiation and based on realistic assessments of the involved entities’ economic and technical capacity. The Bank can help support robust operational arrangements from the outset through appropriate covenants or DLIs. The time between completion and operationalization of facilities with sensitive equipment, such as the center for the production of sterilized keratitis, should be minimal. Ensuring a seamless transition between equipment installation (e.g., air conditioning, filtering, ventilation systems, or other equipment with high maintenance needs) and operationalization can prevent deterioration and subsequent need for costly refitting and repairs. Related to the rearing of insects for biological pest control, it is key to ensure careful calibration and stress testing of the air conditioning system to provide sufficiently stable and conducive conditions for breeding activities.
