AB  - Ratings for the Integrated Disaster Risk Management (DRM) and Resilience Program-for-Results (PforR) Project for Morocco were as follows: outcome was highly satisfactory, Bank performance was satisfactory, and monitoring and evaluation (M and E) quality was substantial. Some lessons learned included: comprehensive program design and government commitment enabling simultaneous efforts on all fronts - institutional, investment and policy - is required to uplift DRM and disaster risk financing (DRF) systems. Counterparts’ implementation readiness supported by sustained technical assistance (TA) is crucial. The DRF agenda should be integrated within the overarching financial sector development vision. The program showed that a PforR instrument can be highly effective in promoting scalable and interlinked DRM-DRF solutions. Flexible program design is crucial for maintaining relevance in moments of challenges and opportunities. The sustainability of structural investments co-financed by the Fund for the Fight Against Natural Disasters (FLCN) remains a focus of attention, with the Independent Verification Agent (IVA) emphasizing the need to adopt dedicated operation and maintenance mechanisms.
